Thinking process (10 tools used)\
MiroThinker already implements several forms of dynamic context injection, so the question is really whether a more formalized/generalized version would add incremental value. Here's the analysis:\
\
What MiroThinker already does\
ADK agent (newer architecture)\
The ADK agent has a blackboard pattern where session state carries template variables that agents read dynamically each iteration:\
\
\{research_findings\} \'97 refreshed by maestro_condition_callback after each loop iteration\
\{corpus_for_synthesis\} \'97 updated corpus for the synthesiser\
\{research_strategy\} \'97 thinker's output consumed by the maestro pipeline.py:41-61\
This is already a form of "inject dynamic context" \'97 the thinker sees an ever-richer corpus briefing on each iteration, and the synthesiser reads the swarm-synthesised report via \{corpus_for_synthesis\}: synthesiser.py:32-34\
\
Additionally, three plugins and callbacks inject context dynamically:\
\
GlobalInstructionPlugin \'97 injects static dedup rules into every agent's system prompt at runtime __init__.py:115-125\
\
before_model_callback \'97 dynamically injects a wrap-up instruction when context tokens exceed MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS before_model.py:153-172\
\
_init_pipeline_state \'97 injects initial corpus keys and runs a Phase 0 scout before the pipeline starts pipeline.py:93-108\
\
Miroflow agent (older architecture)\
The miroflow agent generates the system prompt once at the start of run_main_agent and it stays fixed for the entire run (up to 200-300 turns): orchestrator.py:795-800\
\
It does inject failure experience summaries on retries (a form of dynamic context), but the system prompt itself is static throughout a run. answer_generator.py:170-254\
\
Where "inject dynamic context" could add value\
The ADK agent's blackboard pattern is already quite close to a formalized "inject dynamic context" pattern. The main gaps are:\
\
1. Miroflow agent's static system prompt\
Over 200+ turns, the agent's goals and strategy may evolve, but the system prompt never changes. A dynamic context injection could update it mid-run with accumulated knowledge or shifting priorities. The ADK agent solves this with the blackboard, but the miroflow agent doesn't have an equivalent.\
\
2. Turn-aware / budget-aware guidance\
Currently, the only dynamic injection based on resource consumption is the hard context-limit wrap-up. A more graduated approach could inject guidance like "you've used 150/200 turns \'97 start converging on an answer" or "you've spent $8 of your $10 budget \'97 prioritize high-value searches."\
\
3. Cross-run memory\
Neither architecture injects context from previous sessions or runs (beyond the explicit failure-experience retry mechanism). A dynamic context pattern could pull in relevant findings from prior research on similar topics.\
\
Verdict\
For the ADK agent (apps/adk-agent/): marginal value. The blackboard + template variables + callbacks already implement this pattern effectively. Formalizing it further would mostly be an abstraction/naming exercise.\
\
For the miroflow agent (apps/miroflow-agent/): moderate value. The static system prompt over 200+ turns is a real limitation. Injecting a dynamic "here's what you've found so far / here's your remaining budget" section into the system prompt on each turn would help the agent make better decisions as the run progresses. However, this is the older architecture \'97 the ADK agent already addresses this with its blackboard design.\
\
Bottom line: The pattern is already the core design principle of the ADK pipeline agent. If you're working primarily with the miroflow agent, adding a before_model hook that injects a dynamic context summary (accumulated findings, turn budget, strategy shifts) into the system prompt would be a meaningful improvement. If you're on the ADK agent, you already have it.\
\
