Thinking process (8 tools used)\
The core bottleneck you're identifying is real and specific. Today, format_for_thinker() dumps every finding as verbal prose directly into \{research_findings\}. That text must fit in a single LLM context window (~128K tokens). The corpus is hard-capped by whatever one model call can hold. corpus_store.py:2145-2154\
\
Meanwhile, the gossip swarm \'97 which can digest arbitrarily large corpora by partitioning into angle-based workers \'97 only runs once, at the very end, before the final synthesiser: pipeline.py:157-174\
\
The thinker never benefits from it. It reads raw findings, not swarm-digested knowledge.\
\
The architectural shift\
What you're describing is: make the gossip swarm the thinker's sensory system. The thinker doesn't read the corpus directly \'97 the swarm reads it for the thinker and presents a compressed, synthesised briefing. The thinker stays pure, tool-free, world-unaware. It just receives increasingly rich digested knowledge and ponders.\
