I misunderstood your vision. Let me restate it correctly.\
\
What you're actually describing\
The thinker is not a single LLM call that reads a compressed briefing. The thinker is a swarm \'97 a chain of reasoning instances that collectively process the entire corpus, raw and uncompressed. Every instance's output is immutably persisted, creating a traceable lineage of thought. The thinker doesn't receive pre-digested summaries from a synthesis swarm \'97 the thinker IS the constant synthesiser.\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
