The critical properties:\
\
Property	Meaning\
Thinker sees everything	No compression, no pre-synthesis. Every atomic condition passes through the thinker.\
Immutable reasoning	Each thinker instance's output is append-only, persisted to disk. Never overwritten.\
Lineage of thought	You can trace: "at reasoning v3, the thinker had seen chunks 1-3 and concluded X. At v4, after seeing chunk 4, it revised to Y."\
Thinker IS the synthesiser	There's no separate synthesis step. The thinker's job is continuous synthesis \'97 integrating each new chunk into its evolving understanding.\
Sensory swarm feeds raw	The search executor and maestro don't pre-digest. They dump raw data into the corpus. The thinker processes it.\
How this differs from the current architecture\
The current thinker is a single LLM call that reads format_for_thinker() \'97 a verbal prose dump of the entire corpus, bounded by the context window (~128K tokens): corpus_store.py:2145-2154\
\
The current reasoning capture truncates to 5000 chars and is stored for observability only \'97 it's never fed back into the reasoning chain: after_model.py:74-86\
\
The current gossip swarm compresses \'97 workers independently summarise, queen merges. This is lossy. Your vision is lossless \'97 the thinker sees every atom: corpus_store.py:2514-2522\
\
The architecture: streaming fold with persistent reasoning\
The thinker becomes a fold/reduce over the corpus. Each step:\
\
Reads: [accumulated reasoning so far] + [next chunk of raw corpus]\
Outputs: updated reasoning (synthesis, gaps, contradictions, strategy)\
Persists: output is immutably written to disk (append-only reasoning log)\
Feeds forward: output becomes the "accumulated reasoning" for the next step\
This is not gossip (parallel workers \uc0\u8594  merge). This is a sequential chain where each link builds on all prior links. The swarm aspect comes from:\
\
Parallelism across angles: multiple chains can run simultaneously on different research angles, each building their own reasoning lineage\
Parallelism across iterations: as the sensory swarm feeds new data, new fold passes run over the updated corpus, building on the previous pass's final reasoning\
The key insight: the context window is no longer a limit on corpus size. It's a limit on chunk size. A 10,000-finding corpus gets processed in 200 chunks of 50, with reasoning accumulating across all 200 steps. The thinker has "seen" everything \'97 just not all at once.\
\
What already exists as building blocks\
Immutable persistence infrastructure \'97 the event store already has append-only event logging, corpus snapshots per iteration, and LLM trace capture: event_store.py:1-23\
\
Reasoning trace capture \'97 after_model_callback already extracts reasoning content from model responses, but truncates it and doesn't feed it forward: after_model.py:28-86\
\
Knowledge graph persistence \'97 JSONL-backed, append-on-mutation, entities + edges. This is already an immutable-ish knowledge structure: knowledge_graph.py:31-76\
\
The deprecated loop_synthesiser \'97 this was the closest ancestor to your vision. It was an in-loop synthesis step whose output was re-ingested into the corpus. But it was a single LLM call, not a swarm, and it was deprecated: loop_synthesiser.py:1-28\
\
DuckDB corpus with file-backed persistence \'97 the corpus already persists across sessions and supports session continuation: corpus_store.py:1-19\
\
AtomicCondition with full provenance \'97 each finding already carries parent lineage, strategy, expansion depth, angle, iteration: atomic_condition.py:1-52\
\
What needs to be built\
The core new component is a ReasoningLog \'97 an append-only, file-backed store of thinker reasoning snapshots. Each entry is immutable and carries:\
\
Version number (monotonically increasing)\
The chunk of corpus it processed\
The accumulated reasoning it inherited from the previous version\
The new reasoning it produced\
Timestamp, iteration, angle\
The thinker agent changes from a single Agent to a programmatic loop (like the search executor \'97 no LLM orchestration overhead) that:\
\
Queries the corpus for the next unprocessed chunk\
Reads the latest reasoning snapshot from the ReasoningLog\
Calls the thinker model with [latest reasoning] + [new chunk]\
Persists the output to the ReasoningLog\
Repeats until all chunks are processed\
The thinker stays pure \'97 no tools, no world awareness. It just receives text (prior reasoning + new data) and outputs text (updated reasoning). The loop machinery around it is programmatic, like the search executor.\
\
The sensory swarm (search executor + maestro) continues to dump raw data into the corpus. The thinker-fold processes it. The final output of the fold IS the synthesis \'97 no separate synthesiser needed.\
\
Implement thinker-as-fold with immutable reasoning log\
In repo OrpingtonClose/MiroThinker, implement the "thinker as constant synthesiser" architecture where the thinker is a sequential fold over the entire corpus with immutable, persisted reasoning.\
