Why this is better than text injection\
Text injection	Agent injection\
Context window	Single agent must hold everything	Each agent has its own window\
Specialization	One prompt tries to cover everything	Each agent is a domain specialist\
Parallelism	Sequential \'97 one agent processes all	Parallel \'97 multiple agents process simultaneously\
Lineage	Hard to trace which text influenced what	Each agent's output is a distinct row_type='thought' row with parent_id\
Reactivity	Static \'97 injected at fixed points	Dynamic \'97 agents spawned based on what the thinker needs\
Composability	Monolithic prompt engineering	Modular \'97 add/remove agents without changing the thinker\
How it maps to the existing architecture\
The key realization: the maestro is the natural agent spawner. It already has unrestricted Flock SQL access and can see the full corpus state. Today it runs scoring, dedup, and clustering. In this pattern, it would also:\
\
Read the thinker's strategy and the corpus state\
Decide what specialist agents are needed (e.g., "the thinker is pondering pricing but we have 200 pricing findings across 5 angles \'97 spawn a pricing specialist to digest them")\
Spawn agents with curated contexts (SQL query \uc0\u8594  filtered findings \u8594  agent prompt)\
Collect their output and insert it as row_type='thought' rows in the conditions table\
The maestro already has execute_flock_sql() which can run LLM calls inside SQL. A Flock llm_complete() call with a curated context IS essentially a specialist agent \'97 it's an LLM call with a specific prompt and a specific slice of data. The gossip workers are already implemented this way (via _http_complete). maestro.py:1-34\
\
So the implementation path is:\
\
The maestro reads the thinker's strategy\
It queries the corpus to identify clusters/angles that need specialist reasoning\
For each cluster, it runs a Flock llm_complete() with a curated prompt (the "agent")\
The output is inserted as row_type='thought' with parent_id linking to the relevant findings\
The thinker reads these thought rows on the next iteration \'97 it sees specialist reasoning, not raw data\
The thinker stays pure. It never touches tools. It never sees the raw corpus. It sees agent-produced thoughts \'97 curated, specialized reasoning from dynamically spawned specialists. The "injected context" is the specialist agent itself.\
\
The elegant part\
