MiroThinker: Thought Swarm Architecture\
A unified design document synthesising the full architectural vision discussed for OrpingtonClose/MiroThinker.\
\
1. Current Architecture\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
The pipeline is a SequentialAgent wrapping a LoopAgent (max 3 iterations) followed by a final synthesiser. pipeline.py:248-260\
\
Data flows via session state (blackboard):\
\
The thinker reads \{research_findings\} \'97 a verbal prose briefing tiered by quality \'97 and outputs strategy to state["research_strategy"]. It has zero tools. thinker.py:40-52\
\
The search executor reads expansion targets from the corpus + queries from the thinker's strategy. Fires APIs programmatically. No LLM. search_executor.py:405-432\
\
The maestro reads \{research_findings\} + \{research_strategy\}, has unrestricted Flock SQL access via execute_flock_sql(). Its after_agent_callback refreshes state with the updated corpus. maestro.py:46-64\
\
The gossip swarm runs a 3-phase protocol (per-angle workers \uc0\u8594  peer refinement \u8594  queen merge) before the final synthesiser. corpus_store.py:2514-2522\
\
The final synthesiser polishes the swarm output into a publication-quality report. synthesiser.py:25-62\
\
Existing dynamic context injection mechanisms:\
\
Mechanism	Where	What it does\
Blackboard template variables	\{research_findings\}, \{corpus_for_synthesis\}, \{research_strategy\}	Session state injected into agent prompts each iteration\
GlobalInstructionPlugin	plugins/__init__.py	Static dedup rules injected into every agent's system prompt\
before_model_callback	callbacks/before_model.py	Wrap-up instruction injected when context tokens exceed threshold\
_init_pipeline_state	agents/pipeline.py	Corpus keys + Phase 0 scout injected before pipeline starts\
maestro_condition_callback	callbacks/condition_manager.py	Refreshes research_findings after each maestro run\
The corpus \'97 single-table architecture in DuckDB:\
\
All data lives in one conditions table with parent_id/related_id for hierarchical relationships and row_type to discriminate atoms ('finding', 'similarity', 'contradiction', 'raw', 'synthesis'). corpus_store.py:214-284\
\
The thinker receives a verbal prose briefing via format_for_thinker() \'97 findings tiered by composite quality, contradictions called out, under-explored areas identified. corpus_store.py:2145-2154\
\
2. Three Universal Principles\
These apply to both the fixed-run and continuous architectures. There are no strong reasons to make them mode-specific \'97 they are properties of the thought system itself, not of any particular execution model.\
\
2.1 Immutable Lineage\
Every thought, every reasoning trace, every context mutation is persisted to disk and never modified or deleted. This creates a traceable lineage of thought \'97 what the thinker was thinking at any point, what information it had, how its reasoning evolved.\
\
Current violation: Reasoning is truncated to 5000 chars and stored for observability only:\
\
\
state["reasoning_traces"].append(\{  \
    "agent": agent_name,  \
    "reasoning": reasoning_text[:5000],  # cap to avoid state bloat  \
    "response_preview": response_text[:500],  \
\})\
after_model.py:78-82\
\
This is unacceptable. Full reasoning must be persisted \'97 no truncation, ever. The fact column in the conditions table is TEXT NOT NULL with no size limit, so full reasoning text fits naturally. corpus_store.py:216-217\
\
Implementation: Thought lineage lives in the Flock table as row_type='thought' rows \'97 the same parent-child SQL pattern already used for every other row type:\
\
\
-- Every row already has parent-child relationships  \
parent_id INTEGER,  \
related_id INTEGER,\
corpus_store.py:225-227\
\
Similarity rows already use this exact pattern \'97 parent_id points to one condition, related_id to the other: atomic_condition.py:45-48\
\
Thought rows follow the same convention:\
\
fact \uc0\u8594  full reasoning text (NO truncation)\
row_type \uc0\u8594  'thought'\
parent_id \uc0\u8594  previous thought in the chain\
strategy \uc0\u8594  the visible output / strategy extracted from reasoning\
angle \uc0\u8594  agent name or research angle\
iteration \uc0\u8594  pipeline iteration\
consider_for_use \uc0\u8594  TRUE (the thinker reads its own prior thoughts)\
Lineage is queryable via standard SQL:\
\
\
-- Full thought chain for a given thought  \
WITH RECURSIVE chain AS (  \
    SELECT * FROM conditions WHERE id = ?  \
    UNION ALL  \
    SELECT c.* FROM conditions c JOIN chain ON c.id = chain.parent_id  \
    WHERE c.row_type = 'thought'  \
)  \
SELECT * FROM chain ORDER BY id;\
No new tables. No new infrastructure. Just a new row_type in the existing single-table architecture.\
\
2.2 Arbitrarily Large Context\
No single LLM call needs to hold the entire corpus. The swarm architecture decomposes the corpus into chunks that individual agents can handle. The swarm collectively represents the full context \'97 each agent carries a piece of it with understanding, not just text.\
\
This is what enables hour-long deep research runs. The corpus grows without bound; the swarm scales with it.\
\
2.3 Academic Detachment\
The thought swarm is sovereign. External processes cannot directly modify, delete, or suppress thoughts. The maestro cannot kill thoughts it doesn't like \'97 it can only introduce counter-evidence via new data-bearing agents. Thought rows are immutable in the Flock table:\
\
\
SACRED RULE: Rows with row_type='thought' are IMMUTABLE. You may NEVER  \
UPDATE, DELETE, or set consider_for_use=FALSE on thought rows.\
This ensures intellectual integrity \'97 the lineage of thought is a faithful record, not a curated narrative.\
\
3. The Thought Swarm\
3.1 Core Concept\
The thinker is an oblivious idiot god of pondering \'97 completely tool-free, with no awareness of the external world. It endlessly reasons about whatever information appears in its context. It is tended by a swarm of servant agents that observe its thoughts and inject it with the things it ponders about.\
\
The thinker becomes the constant-synthesiser. It doesn't receive pre-digested summaries \'97 it receives raw information and its job is to continuously integrate it into its evolving understanding. Every piece of information in the system is available to it (via the swarm mechanism).\
\
3.2 Context Injection = Agent Injection\
"Injecting dynamic context" means introducing new agents to the swarm with curated contexts. The thought swarm does not read the Flock table directly. All contact with the outside world is via introducing agents carrying data \'97 data gifts disguised as one of the swarm's own.\
\
Traditional context injection	Agent injection\
Modify an existing agent's prompt	Spawn a new agent carrying the context\
Single context window must hold everything	Each agent has its own window\
Monolithic prompt engineering	Modular \'97 add/remove agents without changing the thinker\
Hard to trace which text influenced what	Each agent's output is a distinct row_type='thought' row with parent_id\
3.3 The Mutable Swarm\
The swarm is a completely mutable set of agents \'97 a flexible context capable of containing arbitrarily large information with full conversational understanding. Agents can be:\
\
Created \'97 a new specialist joins with curated findings\
Retired \'97 a specialist whose understanding is superseded\
Merged \'97 two overlapping specialists consolidated into one\
Split \'97 one specialist whose domain grew too large becomes two\
Refreshed \'97 a specialist gets new data and re-processes\
The swarm IS the context. A context window holds text; an agent holds understanding.\
\
3.4 Internal Architecture\
The thought swarm uses constant gossip \'97 agents continuously share and refine their understanding. Two approaches to context preservation:\
\
Immutable context cores \'97 each agent has a part of its context that it never loses (its founding data gift)\
Lineage-backed reconstruction \'97 every mutation of every agent's context is recorded as row_type='thought' rows in the Flock table (unknown to the thought agents themselves). If an agent's context degrades, it can be reconstructed from the lineage.\
This is where max-reasoning algorithms become critical. The swarm's internal architecture is not about tool use or search \'97 it's about pure reasoning at maximum depth. The gossip protocol ensures that insights propagate across agents, contradictions surface, and the collective understanding converges.\
\
The gossip swarm workers in _synthesise_gossip are the embryonic form of this \'97 dynamically created agents with curated contexts, using peer refinement: corpus_store.py:2528-2555 corpus_store.py:2562-2586\
\
But they're ephemeral and single-purpose (synthesis only). Thought swarm agents are persistent (their understanding lives as thought rows) and multi-purpose (they reason, not just synthesise).\
\
4. The Maestro as Swarm Gardener\
The maestro's role evolves from "Flock conductor running scoring steps" to gardener of the thought swarm. It already has unrestricted Flock SQL access and can see the full corpus state: maestro.py:1-34\
\
In the new architecture, the maestro:\
\
Reads the thinker's strategy and the corpus state\
Decides what specialist agents are needed ("the thinker is pondering pricing but we have 200 pricing findings across 5 angles \'97 spawn a pricing specialist")\
Spawns agents with curated contexts (SQL query \uc0\u8594  filtered findings \u8594  Flock llm_complete() call)\
Collects their output and inserts it as row_type='thought' rows\
The thinker sees these thought rows on the next iteration \'97 specialist reasoning, not raw data\
The maestro influences the swarm only by introducing data-bearing agents. It cannot kill thoughts \'97 it has to convince the swarm by introducing counter-evidence.\
\
4.1 Maestro as Mixture of Experts\
The maestro doesn't need large context \'97 it needs brutally harsh raw thinking power. This suggests a mixture-of-experts approach:\
\
Operation	Model characteristic needed\
Contradiction detection	Strong logical reasoning (o3, Claude Opus)\
Redundancy compression	Strong summarization (Gemini, GPT-4o)\
Scoring/evaluation	Calibrated judgment\
Agent spawning (crafting curated contexts)	Strong instruction-following\
Strategic decisions	Most powerful reasoning model available\
The model configuration already supports separate models per role: model_config.py:22-36\
\
The Flock proxy routes through LiteLLM, which supports any provider. Currently there's one corpus_model registered: corpus_store.py:189-207\
\
The MoE approach would register multiple models \'97 scoring_model, reasoning_model, synthesis_model \'97 and the maestro would choose which to use for each execute_flock_sql() call:\
\
\
-- Contradiction detection: use the reasoning specialist  \
SELECT llm_complete(\{'model_name': 'reasoning_model'\}, ...) ...  \
  \
-- Summarization: use the synthesis specialist  \
SELECT llm_complete(\{'model_name': 'synthesis_model'\}, ...) ...\
5. Flock's Role \'97 Separation of Concerns\
Flock remains the data management layer \'97 SQL queries as blocks of utility, easily divisible and alterable. The thought swarm is the reasoning layer. This separation must be maintained:\
\
Layer	Responsibility	Mechanism\
Flock (data)	Storage, scoring, dedup, clustering, expansion tracking	DuckDB + Flock SQL\
Thought swarm (reasoning)	Synthesis, integration, inference, narrative	Agent gossip + thought rows\
Maestro (orchestration)	Decides what operations to run, spawns agents, tends the garden	execute_flock_sql() + agent spawning\
Search executor (sensing)	Fires APIs, ingests raw data	Programmatic, no LLM\
The thought swarm does not read the Flock table directly. The maestro mediates \'97 it reads the table, decides what the swarm needs, and introduces data-bearing agents. The Flock table records everything (including thought lineage), but the swarm is unaware of this recording.\
\
The question of "periodic flush of the entire Flock table into the thought swarm" resolves naturally: there is no wholesale flush. The maestro continuously manages the swarm \'97 reading the corpus, deciding which agents to spawn/refresh/retire based on what the thinker needs and what the corpus contains. It's event-driven, not batch.\
\
6. Periodic Synthesis Reports\
The current synthesiser runs once at the end. In the new architecture, synthesis is triggered periodically so the user can observe progress \'97 a readable report at regular intervals.\
\
The existing run_swarm_synthesis(state) and synthesiser_agent already do this work: condition_manager.py:560-565 synthesiser.py:64-75\
\
Periodic synthesis reports are stored as row_type='synthesis' rows in the conditions table (this row type already exists). The synthesis row's parent_id points to the latest thought, linking the report to the reasoning chain that produced it. A configurable interval (SYNTHESIS_INTERVAL) controls frequency.\
\
7. Two Execution Modes\
7.1 Fixed-Run Mode (current, proven)\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
The current LoopAgent(max_iterations=3) structure stays. Each run is an episode. The DuckDB file persists on disk between runs, so the thought swarm's lineage carries across sessions: condition_manager.py:608-613\
\
The user asks for something, gets a report, then comments on it \'97 expanding arbitrarily. Each follow-up reopens the same DuckDB corpus. This produces exceptional results today and the UX is natural. server.py:371-375\
\
The three universal principles (immutable lineage, arbitrarily large context, academic detachment) apply fully. The thought swarm operates within each run, and its lineage persists across runs via the DuckDB file.\
\
7.2 Continuous Mode (future)\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
The pipeline becomes unbounded \'97 no max_iterations, no fixed phases. The maestro continuously tends the swarm. The stall detector already supports this: "run as long as you keep making progress; die if you go silent." main.py:26-31\
\
This opens the design space for hour-long deep research (comparable to OpenAI's deep research). The time horizon of analysis becomes a parameter, not a constraint.\
\
The dashboard becomes a living knowledge tree. The current dashboard already has ReactFlow for graph visualization and SSE streaming at 500ms intervals: PipelineGraph.tsx:266-298\
\
In continuous mode, the fixed 6-node pipeline graph transforms into an ever-expanding knowledge tree \'97 each node a row_type='thought' row, each edge a parent_id link. Presentation options:\
\
Tree view \'97 parent-child thought lineage, expandable/collapsible\
Timeline view \'97 thoughts ordered chronologically, corpus size growing\
Angle view \'97 thoughts grouped by research angle, showing deepening\
Contradiction view \'97 thought pairs that conflict, resolution chains\
Synthesis milestones \'97 periodic reports as checkpoint nodes\
Continuous mode has rough edges that need figuring out (session management, cost control, convergence criteria, user interaction mid-run). Fixed-run mode is proven and ships today. The three universal principles ensure that the transition from fixed to continuous is an evolution, not a rewrite \'97 the same DuckDB corpus, the same thought rows, the same immutable lineage.\
\
