\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 The mechanism of improvement is structural elimination of the tool invocation cycle. Tool-based approaches require: (1) agent recognition of temporal information need, (2) tool selection from available options, (3) call formulation with appropriate parameters, (4) network round-trip and execution, (5) result parsing and integration, and (6) subsequent reasoning incorporating retrieved information. Dynamic injection collapses this to single-step availability: current time is computed and formatted by the hosting infrastructure, appearing in system prompt without agent cognitive overhead .\cb1 \
\cb3 Scaling implications are substantial. At one million agent calls monthly, the 95% token reduction translates to hundreds to thousands of dollars in direct API cost savings, exclusive of latency-related infrastructure efficiency and user experience improvements. The pattern establishes a general principle: information already available to the orchestrating system should be proactively provided rather than requiring agent retrieval. This principle extends beyond temporal data to user profiles, environmental state, configuration parameters, and any predictably needed information.\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
