\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 For folder references, intelligent summarization replaces raw content enumeration: directory structure overviews, representative file samples, or AI-generated collection summaries preserve contextual awareness without exhausting token budgets . Security architecture is critical\'97allowlist-based directory access, file type filtering, size limits, and credential scanning prevent unauthorized access and information leakage.\cb1 \
\cb3 The pattern enables sophisticated research workflows: iterative document exploration where users progressively refine context through targeted references, multi-source synthesis with automatic provenance tracking, and collaborative analysis where team members share context through standardized path conventions. The cognitive efficiency of reference-over-copy transforms interaction fluidity, maintaining task focus without manual content management overhead.\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 1.3.3 API return value embedding directly into context\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 API return value embedding extends dynamic injection to structured external data sources, enabling agents to reason about live system states without explicit tool invocation . Rather than exposing APIs as tools requiring agent-directed access, the system proactively retrieves and embeds relevant data based on predicted needs or configured triggers.\cb1 \
\cb3 The implementation architecture involves: predictive analysis identifying information needs from conversation state or explicit indicators; efficient data fetching with caching, batching, and refresh policies; format transformation converting structured API responses into model-interpretable representations; and budget-aware integration that balances information richness against token constraints.\cb1 \
\cb3 Value proposition is strongest for high-frequency, predictable information needs where tool overhead would dominate. Customer service agents receive real-time order status and account information; research agents access current publication metrics and trending topics; financial analysis agents incorporate live market data and portfolio positions. In each case, proactive embedding eliminates decision latency and invocation overhead while maintaining information currency through automated refresh cycles.\cb1 \
\cb3 The hybrid design pattern combines proactive embedding for high-confidence needs with reactive tool access for unpredictable requirements. This optimizes the efficiency-flexibility trade-off: common information paths are accelerated through injection, while edge cases remain supported through full tool capabilities.\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 \cb3 2. MiroThinker-Specific Context Architecture\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 2.1 Native Context Management in MiroThinker-1.7\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 2.1.1 Context operator (\uc0\u934 \u8348 ): Transforms trajectory log H\u8348 \u8317 \uc0\u7497 \uc0\u8318  into effective context C\u8348 \u8317 \uc0\u7497 \uc0\u8318 \cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 MiroThinker-1.7 implements sophisticated learned context management through the context operator \uc0\u934 \u8348 , a mathematical transformation that converts raw trajectory logs into optimized context representations for LLM inference . This operator addresses the fundamental compression challenge of long-horizon agent execution: research trajectories can involve hundreds of tool calls and observations, quickly exceeding practical context limits without intelligent management.\cb1 \
\cb3 The formal structure defines trajectory log H\uc0\u8348 \u8317 \uc0\u7497 \uc0\u8318  = \{(T\u8321 , A\u8321 , O\u8321 ), ..., (T\u8348 \u8331 \u8321 , A\u8348 \u8331 \u8321 , O\u8348 \u8331 \u8321 )\} capturing thoughts T\uc0\u7522 , actions A\uc0\u7522 , and observations O\uc0\u7522  at each step . The context operator produces effective context C\uc0\u8348 \u8317 \uc0\u7497 \uc0\u8318  = \{(T\uc0\u7522 , A\uc0\u7522 , \uc0\u934 \u8348 (O\uc0\u7522 ))\}\uc0\u7522 \uc0\u8332 \u8321 \uc0\u7511 \uc0\u8315 \'b9 through selective observation transformation while preserving complete thought-action traces. This asymmetry reflects empirical insight: reasoning continuity depends on thought-action visibility, while observations contain compressible redundancy.\cb1 \
\cb3 The operator's learned parameters enable optimization for specific task distributions. Rather than fixed heuristics, MiroThinker's implementation trains compression strategies that preserve information most relevant to successful task completion, adapting to patterns of information value across different research domains and query types . This learning-based approach distinguishes MiroThinker from simpler truncation-based alternatives, enabling more sophisticated trade-offs between compression ratio and information preservation.\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 2.1.2 Sliding window mechanism: Retains recent steps, truncates older observations\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The sliding window mechanism implements the context operator's compression through recency-biased retention with mathematically precise structure . The window is defined by index set S\uc0\u8348 (K) = \{i 
\f4 \uc0\u8712 
\f1  \{1,...,t-1\} | i \uc0\u8805  t-K\}, selecting the K most recent steps for full observation retention.\cb1 \
