\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 The K=5 configuration in MiroThinker-1.7 reflects empirical optimization: extending retention beyond five steps yielded diminishing returns at substantial token cost . This aggressive compression might seem counterintuitive, but aligns with observed agent behavior where recent context dominates current reasoning relevance, and earlier information is either incorporated into persistent belief states (captured in thought traces) or genuinely superseded.\cb1 \
\cb3 The mechanism's effectiveness is validated through benchmark performance: MiroThinker-1.7 achieves 74.0% on BrowseComp, 75.3% on BrowseComp-ZH, 82.7% on GAIA-Val-165, and 42.9% on HLE-Text\'97establishing state-of-the-art results among open-source research agents . These outcomes demonstrate that well-designed context truncation need not impair reasoning quality when retention policies align with information value patterns.\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 2.1.3 Token budget enforcement: Compresses history to fit within LLM constraints\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Token budget enforcement operates as the hard constraint shaping all context management decisions. MiroThinker-1.7's 256K token context window supports up to 300 tool calls per task (600 in earlier versions) , but even this substantial capacity requires disciplined management for extended trajectories.\cb1 \
