\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Critical tools like \cb10 run_command\cb3  and \cb10 run_python_code\cb3  receive special handling due to unbounded output potential . Without truncation limits, a single verbose execution could exhaust the entire context budget, preventing any subsequent reasoning. The truncation mechanism ensures graceful degradation rather than catastrophic failure, with explicit markers enabling agent awareness of compression and potential follow-up for critical details.\cb1 \
\cb3 The episode restart policy provides additional budget management: when maximum turn budget T\uc0\u8344 \u8336 \u8339  is reached without final answer, the agent discards all prior state and restarts from original query alone . This clean-slate approach avoids bias from potentially degraded context, with final-episode modification ensuring graceful termination by attempting answer extraction even if T\u8344 \u8336 \u8339  is reached again.\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
