\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 This complementarity enables architectural synergy: the context operator ensures coherent long-horizon operation by managing internally generated information, while dynamic injection provides efficient external grounding without disrupting this internal management. Neither mechanism alone suffices\'97pure history management cannot access information outside the trajectory; pure injection lacks mechanisms for maintaining reasoning continuity across extended interactions.\cb1 \
\cb3 The integration challenge is unifying these functions within shared token budgets and attention mechanisms. Injected content competes with historical context for limited capacity, requiring intelligent allocation that reflects relative information value. Preliminary evidence from MiroThinker-1.7-mini suggests this synergy can be optimized: 16.7% better performance with 43% fewer interaction rounds compared to MiroThinker-1.5, indicating that improved context quality can simultaneously enhance efficiency and effectiveness .\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 2.2.2 Integration points: Where injection occurs relative to context operator processing\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Integration point selection fundamentally shapes combined system behavior. Three primary patterns merit consideration for MiroThinker enhancement:\cb1 \
\cb3 Pre-operator injection incorporates external content into raw trajectory H\uc0\u8348  before \u934 \u8348  processing. This subjects injected information to same compression and selection as native observations, enabling unified optimization but risking loss if operator judges external content less critical than trajectory elements. Appropriate when external information should be integrated into coherent historical structure rather than receiving special prominence.\cb1 \
\cb3 Post-operator injection adds content after \uc0\u934 \u8348  produces C\u8348 \u8317 \uc0\u7497 \uc0\u8318 , creating final context C'\u8348 \u8317 \uc0\u7497 \uc0\u8318  = C\u8348 \u8317 \uc0\u7497 \uc0\u8318  \u8853  I. This guarantees injection preservation regardless of trajectory complexity, at cost of consuming tokens that might preserve additional history. Appropriate for high-priority external information that must be accessible: user query specifications, critical constraints, current temporal grounding.\cb1 \
\cb3 Parallel injection maintains separate streams with differential processing: trajectory through sliding window compression, external context through specialized handling (persistent storage, rapid refresh, relevance filtering), combined only at final assembly. This enables sophisticated multi-tier management but increases architectural complexity. Appropriate for deployments with diverse information types requiring distinct lifecycle policies.\cb1 \
\cb3 For MiroThinker specifically, empirical evaluation would guide optimal integration. The current architecture suggests natural extension through post-operator system message augmentation: established framework context (time, user, project) injected before historical context, with user-initiated references (at-mentions, explicit requests) processed as additional post-operator elements.\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 2.2.3 Potential hybrid approaches: Combining sliding window with selective injection\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Hybrid architectures that leverage both MiroThinker's sliding window and dynamic injection capabilities represent promising research and development directions:\cb1 \
\cb3 Adaptive window sizing adjusts K based on injection requirements. When substantial external context is injected, K contracts to preserve budget; when minimal injection occurs, K expands for richer history retention. This dynamic budget allocation optimizes joint information capacity based on actual rather than predicted context composition.\cb1 \
\cb3 Protected injection slots reserve fixed capacity for critical external information that bypasses sliding window compression. Temporal data, user identity, and active constraints receive persistence guarantees, while remaining budget is allocated to trajectory management through standard \uc0\u934 \u8348  processing. This tiered retention reflects information criticality in architectural design.\cb1 \
\cb3 Injection-triggered trajectory summarization responds to significant context shifts by generating compressed summaries of prior trajectory rather than relying solely on sliding window elimination. When new document references or topic changes indicate potential relevance of distant history, targeted summarization preserves essential information in compact form, extending effective memory beyond raw window constraints.\cb1 \
\cb3 Context-aware relevance scoring for injection decisions learns to predict which external information will actually improve task performance, conditioning injection on predicted utility rather than simple availability. This selective injection reduces noise and budget pressure from marginally relevant content, focusing resources on high-impact information incorporation.\cb1 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

